Description: floats one quite full, angling it in towards off. Pushed to mid-off
full length, and on off after hinting to angle in. Flicked towards midwicket
a bit of mix-up, but they are safe in the end. On a good length on off, and tucked to short third off the outside edge. Gurbaz stood still after starting to run, and they eventually made it back
makes some room and skips out, as this short ball on off is swatted to mid-on's right
launched high and wide over long-on!Gurbaz gets into the action. Charges down at this length delivery on the stumps, and sends that 101 metres into the stands

flicked to deep midwicket!This is a bit fuller, but enough for Gurbaz to slam that away off his pads, as there is no movement off the pitch or from it either. Square leg was placed closer in, and that was hit well

Arshdeep strikes first ball!He is celebrating with his arms wide, and with half a sprint down long leg. Good pace and bounce from him though. H pitched it about middle and off, as the ball angled across, and rose rather sharply on off stump. Mandeep pulled, but the extra bounce got him. Straight into deep square leg's hands
good length on fifth stump, and clipped to midwicket. Gurbaz is sent back by Anukul
lofted over mid-on!That bounced just before hitting the rope. Yup, it's a four. He is standing deep in his crease, and ready to launch this length ball angling into him towards middle stump
quite full and wide of off, and he drills that but straight to the extra-cover fielder
good bouncer. Pitches it short on middle, as Anukul first shapes to swing it away, but then ducks last moment, since the line seemed to be almost cramping him

spooned to midwicket!Arsh gets two in this over. I think the extra bounce came into play again, and so did his pace. Another short delivery from Arsh, and this one's line was a bit wide of off, much further away from the middle-stump line he cramped Anukul with previous ball. Anukul pulled, but found the fielder, who didn't have to move at all

strikes first ball, just like Arshdeep!Rinku goes after the legspinner right away, but finds deep midwicket. Chahar bowls on a length on off, but it is the wrong 'un. It turns away from Rinku's arc, as he looks to slog sweep. Instead, the ball ends up landing right into the fielder's lap
dabs this short ball straightening just outside off, and the ball goes past slip
full and flatter on off. Flay-batted to cover
turns away off a short length, and ends wide-ish of off. Hacked to deep point
the googly ends up on leg, after being pitched short on middle and off. Pulled to fine leg
slashes and misses. Short ball, turning away - as it was the wrong 'un again - and ending outside off. Half an appeal for caught behind
full ball on his pads, and flicked to long leg
short, and angling into the stumps. Punched back
hammered just over the bowler's raised hands!That was bashed back dangerously. Shortish ball around off, and swatted back
on the bounce to deep midwicket. Short ball angling into leg, and pulled away again
now Iyer drills on the bounce to extra cover. Full and wide of off, and he attacks at it
goes for the switch hit, but misses the full ball on leg as they pinch a bye off the keeper's pad
misfield by point, as Iyer reverse sweeps this good length ball on off. Shahrukh the fielder there
fired wayyyy over long-off!Gets his front leg out of the way, and launches this length ball on off to get six
short on middle and leg, and quicker with good bounce. Poked to short third, as Iyer is sent back
good length on the stumps, and tapped to point for a hurried run
full delivery on middle, and swept to deep square
full and wide of off, and turning away while bouncing nicely. Russell misses his attempted cut
good length ball, angling in late into middle and off after pitching on off. Stabbed to point
clubbed over mid-off!Stands deep in the crease at this length delivery, which is ending outside off. Russell opened the bat face, and sliced that back forcefully
dropped by short fine running back!Prabhsimran the fielder. Ellis isn't happy, but it didn't look very easy too. It was a slower ball and short on off, and Russell pulled and got a top edge
now bowls a good yorker just outside off. Jammed down to long-off
another yorker, and bowled on fifth stump. Russell slashes and misses
slower ball, and a full length on fifth stump. Swatted without timing to long-on
swats this short and wide ball outside off to deep point
full ball on off, and flicked to deep midwicket
low full toss, and heaved away over wide long-on!Perhaps Curran tried the yorker; anyway, it didn't work. Russell got his front leg out of the way while standing deep in the crease, and flung at that
ramps between point and short third!Not very Russell-like, though. Short delivery, almost cramping him for room while rising on middle. He sways away a bit, and lofts it late

finds deep midwicket!Could be exactly the wrong time for KKR, given there is rain around. Curran went short again, except that this one was an offcutter, which rose sharply after pitching middle and leg, while also angling across. Russell swat-pulled but only off the higher side of the bat

ridiculous!Effortless. Too good. Looked like he never really wanted to hit it that far, yet that shortish ball angling away towards off travelled over deep square leg as Thakur pulled almost with disdain
sliced on the bounce to deep point. Full and wide-ish of off, as Iyer opens the bat face to loft
full ball angling into middle. Whipped to deep backward square

ramped to point!Another bouncer from Arsh earns him a wicket. The bounce was a bit too much for Iyer to handle. Arsh banged it in short around off, with Iyer almost leaping a little to get on top of it. But he ended up half-ramping it - and without any control - to point
full ball on off, and driven to extra cover's right
fires a yorker length ball on off, which is driven to long-on
just over long-on!This game is not over yet. Narine showing what he has got. On a good length on the stumps, and just lofted with the least of efforts
woah, that looked to effortless!Just high elbows, and the full face of the bat, as it was a length ball in the slot on off. Four over mid-off
opens the bat face to dab this good length ball angling across towards off to point
short in length on middle, and pulled to fine leg
fullish ball on middle and off. Flicked to deep square elg
charges down the track, but Curran bowls short and beats Gurbaz completely. Perhaps Gurbaz skipped out too early after making room, and Curran bowled short on leg. Gurbaz pulled and missed
quite full this time on off, and dragged to mid-on's right. Rishi Dhawan there fumbles, as it could have been tight
shorter side of a length on off, and dabbed to short third. Gurbaz wanted a single, but was sent back
good ball. Sees the batter make room, and fires a yorker on fifth stump, which Gurbaz slashes at but misses
fuller side of a length on leg, and takes his pad as he tries to flick. Again he tries for a single, before going back
four dots in a row. This is called first bouncer, as Arsh bangs it in short on middle and leg. Gurbaz ducks, as the good bounce takes it high above him

flashed just wide of short third!Gurbaz runs out of patience, and jumps out of his crease. The ball ended up being a low, dipping full toss outside off, and the ball takes his outside edge with Gurbaz trying to heave
good length ball angling into off. Punched to cover-point
starts with a slower ball. Full length on off, and he loses his bottom hand while trying to hoick. The ball ends up at cover off his outside edge, and Iyer is just back with the throw arriving there

Ellis pings off stump!This time Ellis had good pace on ball, changing up after that slower delivery last ball. Gurbaz, again trying to be adventurous, makes some room, and also skips out of the crease. He hacks at this good length ball on off - rather it was on the shorter side of a length - and missed, as the stumps lit up
full delivery on off, and defended back
swiped to long leg!Harpreet from deep square leg runs and dives to his left, but in vain. Good length ball on his legs, and pulled away by Rana
a touch fuller than the last ball, and on a good length again on middle and leg. Clipped towards deep midwicket
now much fuller on off, and pushed back
good length darted into middle, and angled in. Iyer misses his pull, and is hit on his pad
shortish just outside off, and pushed to long-on
very full on off, and flicked to midwicket
short outside off, and swatted to mid-off
flicked for four between short fine and square leg!Too quick, and too full, angling into his pads, as Iyer just clipped it using the pace

punched between cover-point and extra cover!The last two balls ruin Raza's over. This was short just outside off, as Iyer pushed late it, with the cover-point fielder diving to his right and missing the ball
good length ball on leg, taking his pads towards fine leg as he looked to clip
good length on middle and leg. Clipped to deep backward square
slower ball on a good length on off. Pushed to extra cover
goes driving, but is beaten!Length delivery angling across, and finishing on sixth stump, as the ball passes his outside edge
makes room, and skips down. Ellis spots that, and bowls on a good length outside leg. Swiped to fine leg
short delivery on middle and off, and pulled to deep backward square
chips this full and flat ball on the stumps just wide of long-on, and they pinch two. Good running
good length, angling into leg. Whipped off his pads to fine leg
short and wide-ish of off. Slashed to deep point
goes low, roundarm, and wide of the crease. Shortish on off, and punched to long-on
switch hit lofted over short third!The fielder ran back all the way, but in vain. Good length on off, and swung away
fullish length angling down leg, as he tried to sweep but missed. They sneak a bye, as the ball went past the keeper too
flung away to deep third!Off the top edge, but that will do. Charges down after making room, as Dhawan bowls on a good length outside off. Rana swung, band eventually got four
a commanding pull!That travelled very quickly over deep midwicket. On the shorter side of a length around middle, and Dhawan's pace isn't that troubling. Rana swung for six
slower ball. Good length, and angling away to end wide of off. Slashed to point
a tennis-batted hack to point, as this ball is a slower ball again, and is short on off. Played that very late there
pulled wide of long-on!Change of pace again from Dhawan, and in vain. He pitched it on the shorter side, angling it across as it ended outside off. Iyer fetched that from there, and crashed that
short of a length on middle and off, and punched to point
stops in his action last moment, and bowls on a length while angling into leg. Swept to short fine

slashed straight to point!Raza is relieved after going for some runs in his first two overs. That was there to be hit, but Rana ended up gifting the fielder an easy catch. Short and slightly wide of off, as Rana went hard at that only to end up walking back. So the time-out breaks his momentum
length ball outside off, hinting to turn away. Pushed to deep point
very full on middle, and whipped to deep midwicket
shortish on off, and clipped to deep backward square. Misfield by Arsh allows a second
good length wide-ish of off, and pushed to deep point
